        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 4:16PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 416 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Cimarron, or 17 miles west of Springer, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cimarron, Philmont Scout Ranch, Miami and Rayado.

This includes the following highways...
Highway 64 between Mile Markers 312 and 315.
Interstate 25 near Mile Marker 411.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
